@startuml
title Chapter 3.05 - Debouncing Pattern Class Model

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype polyline
top to bottom direction

together {
  class main {
    +main(argc, argv)
  }

  class ButtonDriver {
    +oldState : unsigned char
    +toggleOn : unsigned char
    +itsButton : Button*
    +itsMicrowaveEmitter : MicrowaveEmitter*
    +itsTimer : Timer*
    --
    +eventReceive()
  }
}

class Button {
  +deviceState : int
  +backlight : int
  +buttonDriver : ButtonDriver*
  --
  +backlight(light)
  +getState() : int
}

class Timer {
  +time : int
  --
  +delay(time)
}

class MicrowaveEmitter {
  +deviceState : int
  --
  +startEmitting()
  +stopEmitting()
}

together {
  Button -[hidden]-> Timer
  Timer -[hidden]-> MicrowaveEmitter
}

main ..> ButtonDriver : drives example flow

ButtonDriver --> Button : reads button state
ButtonDriver --> Timer : waits debounce interval
ButtonDriver --> MicrowaveEmitter : toggles output

note right of ButtonDriver
Debouncer role.
Waits for signal stability, then
acts only on a valid state change.
end note

note right of Button
Physical input device.
Its signal may bounce.
The code also stores a back-pointer
to ButtonDriver, but it is omitted
here to keep the diagram readable.
end note

note right of Timer
Provides the debounce delay
before re-checking the input.
end note

note right of MicrowaveEmitter
Application device controlled only
after a validated button event.
end note

@enduml
